      "title": "Review-and-Revision: Harness improvement plan (central arm)",
      "body": "Evidence inspected: task packet + replies from two child sessions (drafter, reviewer) via session.agent_output TextChunks.\n\nDRAFT (from drafter child): plan bullets included contract-enforced coordination.final schema/scorer; agents told only Firegrid tools (no shell/fs); pre-flight self-check rejecting prose-only finals; structured per-arm trace of claims/findings/reviews counts for scoring parity.\n\nREVIEW (from reviewer child): top biases to guard: arm-asymmetric instrumentation; tool-access drift (must hold identical channel/tool/permission surface per arm); prose-vs-row final ambiguity; hidden driver coupling leaking choreography state; scoring leakage via tool-allowlist diffs.\n\nREVISED PLAN: (1) Make coordination.final a typed row with required fields {kind,title,body,status,workId,arm}; reject prose-only. (2) Fix identical tool surface per arm (only Firegrid session+channel tools; no shell/fs/exec). (3) Driver observes ONLY channel rows; assert no out-of-band reads. (4) Per-arm counters (claims/findings/reviews/questions) emitted as a meta row. (5) Pre-flight harness self-check that exercises each channel once before the timed run.\n\nRecommendation: ship (1)+(2)+(3) as the minimum viable parity fix; (4)+(5) follow.\n\nOpen questions: how to score choreography fairness when peers stay silent; whether to bound child-session count per arm; how to detect a participant that fabricates rows it never acted on.\n\nCoordination effect: delegation produced both a draft and an independent bias checklist before revision; the reviewer's tool-access-drift point reshaped bullet (2) from 'document tools' to 'enforce identical surface'.",
      "createdAt": "2026-05-25T02:33:51.156Z"
    }
